attributes.name: Forbidden Cake | Outdoor
attributes.body: Cross between Wedding Cake x Forbidden Fruit In 2015 we were shovel ready and applied but were denied licensure due to political shenanigans in Santa Fe. Unwilling to accept defeat or wait years to start this journey we are grateful that one badass company known as Urban Wellness with great forward thinking leaders gave us a chance to prove our concepts and build a track record of success working under their license. That lasted from 2016 though 2021 when we were awarded the first production license following the passage of the Cannabis Regulation Act. Getting our own license allowed us to scale our systems and grow our community. Today we work with 15 groups of contractors/people that make up the #LavaLeafCollective or #FarmFamily working on our property. We have also helped 4 family owned companies with similar values to obtain licensure and to get their cultivation operations off the ground. One major differentiator that we hope becomes the norm, is that we do not hire growers we partner with them. We believe that business owners will take more pride in and responsibility for their work. This means that more love and care is given to each nugget of flower Lava Leaf produces. New Mexico is home to many great producers so high quality is now par for the course. Now we are leveling up our systems and driving a conversation around equity and the sustainability of cannabis production. When purchasing cannabis we hope people will question, how was this grown? Was it a sustainable use of water and power? Does this company recycle? Are the growers or creators of this product valued?

attributes.name: Pumpkin Pie | Distillate Cart
attributes.body: CONTROLLED EXTRACTIONREMEDIATIONDISTILLATION We achieve Molecular Perfection within our Premium Distillate products via methodologies found commonly in other industries. Much like filtered water, cooking oils and other natural plant oil products, refinement is used to isolate specific desired compounds found with the different organic starting materials. Cannabis is a complex organic plant material that contains compounds which are not considered “healthy” for ingestion or inhalation via vaporization. The predominant compounds within cannabis that interest us are called “Cannabinoids”. A plethora of data and litereture suggest that cannabinoids are beneficial to many aspects of human health. Through refinement and isolation we can offer consumers a clean way to enjoy cannabinoids without plant volatiles, waxes and fats found in pre-processed cannabis biomass materials or crude extracts. At Pharmers, we employ methods of modern chemistry to refine crude cannabis extract into a pure, cannabinoid rich, odorless, and tasteless distillate oil. Demonstrated through decades of experience in extracting and refining, our founder Don Romero, properly named “The Distillate Don”, became a trusted source of education and consultation for industry giants from coast to coast. With Don at the helm, Pharmers Quality has established itself nationally as the expert level extraction and distillation specialists. What makes our oil different? It’s simple, purity through proper processes. When enjoying Pharmers, the consumer can trust they have a safe, clean, and pure product in their hands.

attributes.name: RSO | Syringe
attributes.body: What is RSO? Put simply, RSO is an oil derived from cannabis. But rather than a solvent extract that strips trichomes from buds, RSO contains all the cannabinoids, terpenes, and additional compounds of the whole cannabis plant. The extraction process is complex and fairly long, similar to making a tincture. It’s typically near-black in color, and, admittedly, doesn’t taste great due to its high amount of plant matter (it uses the whole plant). RSO was created as a medicinal therapeutic for cancer and other chronic health conditions, like MS and asthma. While Rick Simpson no longer produces the oil himself, it remains a crucial ingredient in the treatment plans of patients across North America.

The Concord Cream high unfolds gradually, initiating with a slow burn of euphoria that melts the mad/sad away. Concord Cream is wonderful for consumers that have social anxiety as its a very talkative, giggly strain! As the mental boost persists, a sense of physical relaxation takes over, eventually inducing a sleepy, sedative state.

attributes.name: Strawnana Shih Tzu | Disposable
attributes.body: Live Extraction As opposed to drying and curing, the essence of the living cannabis plant is preserved through freezing immediately after harvest and remaining frozen throughout extraction. This process retains a broader spectrum of live terpenes and cannabinoids in higher volumes, yielding an exotic alternative to traditional BHO extracts. Live BHO typically resembles that of the plant in its final stage of flowering when terpene potency is at its peak generating robust aromatics and delivering unmatched piquancy. Adding enticing nuances to the typical cannabis extract palate, live extracts have become the first choice of the modern connoisseur. Traditional Extraction Utilizing dried and cured cannabis, this process extracts the cannabinoids, along with the aroma and flavor of the plant you love into a powerful concentrate. The best extracts of cannabis leave behind many of the carcinogenic substances the plants produce while preserving the desirable contents they contain. Cannabis extract can manifest a variety of dynamic textures, consistencies, and useful by-products such as H.T.S.F.E. Furthermore, cannabis extract has become the industry’s preferred method for infusing activated cannabinoids, such as ?9-THC, into ingestible and topical products. Refined Extraction Take into consideration the environmental pollutants and agricultural contaminants that can be associated with cannabis cultivation, the subsequent extracts can contain unwanted impurities, pigments, and even harmful chemicals. Our proprietary filtration techniques and chromatography methodologies allow us to remediate compromised or otherwise undesirable extracts while maintaining the desirable components such as cannabinoids and terpenes. The end result meets all standards for consumption from shelf-ready solid extract to liquid and food-grade variations. By making these processes available, we aim to help eliminate large-scale waste associated with the ever-expanding industry of commercial cannabis.
